A KILLER is being hunted by police after he failed to return to jail while on unescorted leave.James Lieser, 38, did not return to custody at HMP Greenock on Friday after being allowed leave to visit his family in Glasgow.He was last seen by his family in Parkhead, at about 3.30pm that day.An image of Lieser has today been released as the hunt for him continues.In 2004, he was convicted of the murder of Steven Collins in Parkhead on August 23, 2003.A Police Scotland spokesman said: &quot;James Lieser, 38, failed to return to HMP Gateside Prison in Greenock following unescorted leave on Friday April 24.&quot;He was convicted of murder in 2004 and has served 11 years of a 12-year sentence.&quot;Anyone with information on his whereabouts should contact Police Scotland on 101.&quot;